"{\"uid\": \"yardbarker.com-olympics-articles-olympic_breaking_had_its_moment_if_ever_so_brief-s1_13132_40729268\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Olympic debut of breaking, known colloquially as breakdancing, was a highly anticipated event at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers seemed to save the best for last as the men's and women's breaking events were held on the final days of the two-week-long Olympics.\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition was quickly a crowd favorite with bleachersreportedly swayingwith rowdy fans andpacked standing-room-only sections.\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes, known as B-girls and B-boys, went head-to-head asjudges scored their \\\"throwdowns\\\"on six different criteria - creativity, personality, technique, variety, performativity and musicality.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA's B-Boy Victor gets his day underway at the#ParisOlympics.E!\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6920471481115784, \"rank\": 0.2732997339308959, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"and Peacockpic.twitter.com/Xc6RPI2SPZ  Historic first medals were handed out Friday in the women's competition as Japan's Ami Yuasa took gold.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9240104012970308, \"rank\": 0.07568142676681532, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada's Phil Wizard took home top honors in the men's competition on Saturday.\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.5329009832024438, \"rank\": 0.40007410747339944, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the festivities were not all joyous as the dancing concluded.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News spread that the sportwill not return for the 2028 Los Angeles Games, which would make breaking a potential Olympic one-hit wonder.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But organizers of breaking competitions outside the Olympicsvowed to lobby Australian officialsfor inclusion in the 2032 Games in Brisbane.\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1171, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.5988246361231626, \"rank\": 0.6393003082216009, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1226, \"end\": 1234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.996398242640137, \"rank\": 0.0019810197464925983, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our campaign to be added to Brisbane 2032 has already begun and is being ably led by our first vice-president and resident Australian Tony Tilenni,\\\" World Dance Sport Federation president Shawn Tay said in October 2023 when it was first announced breaking would not continue in four years.\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc